"Robine J.-M., Cheung S.L.K., Le Roy S., Van Oyen H., Griffiths C., Michel J.-P., Herrmann F.R.","Death toll exceeded 70,000 in Europe during the summer of 2003",2008,"Comptes Rendus - Biologies","331","2",,"171","178",,,10.1016/j.crvi.2007.12.001,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-38749147699&partnerID=40&md5=dd297f2d48df08053d0b69314c02c4be","INSERM, Démographie et santé, CRLC, parc Euromédecine, 34298 Montpellier cedex 5, France; Unit of Epidemiology, Scientific Institute of Public Health, J. Wytsmanstraat 14, 1050 Bruxelles, Belgium; Office of National Statistics, Mortality Statistics, 1 Drummond Gate, London SW1V 2QQ, United Kingdom; Department of Rehabilitation and Geriatrics, Geneva Medical School and University Hospitals, 3, ch. Pont-Bochet, 1226 Thonex-Genève, Switzerland","Robine, J.-M., INSERM, Démographie et santé, CRLC, parc Euromédecine, 34298 Montpellier cedex 5, France; Cheung, S.L.K., INSERM, Démographie et santé, CRLC, parc Euromédecine, 34298 Montpellier cedex 5, France; Le Roy, S., INSERM, Démographie et santé, CRLC, parc Euromédecine, 34298 Montpellier cedex 5, France; Van Oyen, H., Unit of Epidemiology, Scientific Institute of Public Health, J. Wytsmanstraat 14, 1050 Bruxelles, Belgium; Griffiths, C., Office of National Statistics, Mortality Statistics, 1 Drummond Gate, London SW1V 2QQ, United Kingdom; Michel, J.-P., Department of Rehabilitation and Geriatrics, Geneva Medical School and University Hospitals, 3, ch. Pont-Bochet, 1226 Thonex-Genève, Switzerland; Herrmann, F.R., Department of Rehabilitation and Geriatrics, Geneva Medical School and University Hospitals, 3, ch. Pont-Bochet, 1226 Thonex-Genève, Switzerland","Daily numbers of deaths at a regional level were collected in 16 European countries. Summer mortality was analyzed for the reference period 1998-2002 and for 2003. More than 70,000 additional deaths occurred in Europe during the summer 2003. Major distortions occurred in the age distribution of the deaths, but no harvesting effect was observed in the months following August 2003. Global warming constitutes a new health threat in an aged Europe that may be difficult to detect at the country level, depending on its size. Centralizing the count of daily deaths on an operational geographical scale constitutes a priority for Public Health in Europe. To cite this article: J.-M. Robine et al., C. R. Biologies 331 (2008). © 2007 Académie des sciences.","Daily mortality; Elderly; Europe; Global warming; Heat wave; Human","aging population; elderly population; global warming; mortality; age distribution; article; controlled study; elderly care; Europe; geographic distribution; greenhouse effect; high risk population; human; mortality; public health; seasonal variation; sex difference; summer; Age Distribution; Climate; Death; Europe; Geography; Greenhouse Effect; Hot Temperature; Humans; Mortality; Seasons; Eurasia; Europe",,,,,,"Hémon, D., Jougla, E., La canicule du mois d'août 2003 en France (2004) Rev. Epidemiol. Sante Publique, 52, pp. 3-5; Haines, A., Kovats, R.S., Campbell-Lendrum, D., Corvalan, C., Climate change and human health: impacts, vulnerability, and mitigation (2006) Lancet, 367 (9528), pp. 2101-2109; Kovats, R., Jendritzky, G., Heat waves and human health (2006) Climate Change and Adaptation Strategies for Human Health, p. 449. , Menne B.E., and Kristie L. (Eds), Springer, New York; Sardon, J.-P., Recent demographic trends in developed countries (2006) Population-E, 61 (3), pp. 197-266; Kovats, R., Ebi, K., Heatwaves and public health in Europe (2006) Eur. J. Public Health, 16 (6), pp. 592-599; Meehl, G.A., Tebaldi, C., More intense, more frequent, and longer lasting heat waves in the 21st century (2004) Science, 305 (5686), pp. 994-997; Conti, S., Meli, P., Minelli, G., Solimini, R., Toccaceli, V., Vichi, M., Beltrano, C., Perini, L., Epidemiology study of mortality during the Summer 2003 heat wave in Italy (2005) Environ. Res., 98 (3), pp. 390-399; Garssen, J., Ha